---

<DocLayout title="Interface & Action Types" activeSection="interfaces">

  <h1 class="doc-title" id="custom-interfaces">Interface &amp; Action Types</h1>
  <p class="doc-subtitle">Chapter 7</p>

  <h2 class="section-heading" id="data-types">7.1 Common ROS2 Interface &amp; Action Data Types</h2>
  <p>The following <code class="ph-type">[data_type]</code> can be used for either <code class="ph-var">[message_variable_i]</code>, <code class="ph-var">[request_variable_i]</code>, <code class="ph-var">[response_variable_i]</code>, <code class="ph-var">[goal_variable_i]</code>, <code class="ph-var">[result_variable_i]</code> or <code class="ph-var">[feedback_variable_i]</code>.</p>

  <div class="table-container">
    <table class="doc-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Data Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>bool</td>
          <td>Boolean</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>int8<br>int16<br>int32<br>int64</td>
          <td>Signed integers (8, 16, 32, or 64 bits)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>uint8<br>uint16<br>uint32<br>uint64</td>
          <td>Unsigned integers (8, 16, 32, or 64 bits)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>float32<br>float64</td>
          <td>Floating-point numbers (32 or 64 bits)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>UTF-8 encoded string</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>char</td>
          <td>ASCII character (alias for uint8)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>byte</td>
          <td>Raw byte (alias for uint8)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>builtin_interfaces/Time</td>
          <td>ROS 2 time (seconds + nanoseconds)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>builtin_interfaces/Duration</td>
          <td>Duration (seconds + nanoseconds)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>&lt;package&gt;/msg/&lt;MessageType&gt;</td>
          <td>Custom message type from another package</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>type[]</td>
          <td>Array of a type (variable length)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>type[N]</td>
          <td>Array of a type (fixed length)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>


  <h2 class="section-heading" id="interface-structure">7.2 Structure of Interfaces &amp; Action Types</h2>
  <p>Interfaces are organized by packages, and then by messages (msg) or services (srv).</p>

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.2.1 Message Interfaces</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={msgInterfaceCode} lang="bash" customHtml={msgInterfaceCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.2.2 Service Interfaces</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={srvInterfaceCode} lang="bash" customHtml={srvInterfaceCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.2.3 Action Types</h3>
  <CodeBlock code={actionInterfaceCode} lang="bash" customHtml={actionInterfaceCustom} showLegend={true} />


  <h2 class="section-heading" id="using-interfaces">7.3 Using Interfaces &amp; Actions</h2>

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.3.1 Common Standard ROS 2 Interfaces</h3>
  <p>Before making a custom ROS 2 interface, verify if the functionality you require already exists within an interface already packaged with ROS 2</p>
  
  <div class="table-container">
    <table class="doc-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Message / Service Type</th>
          <th>Fields</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>std_msgs/msg/Float64</td>
          <td>data: float64</td>
          <td>Standard double variable</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>std_msgs/msg/Bool</td>
          <td>data: bool</td>
          <td>Standard boolean variable</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>geometry_msgs/msg/Vector3</td>
          <td>x: float64<br>y: float64<br>z: float64</td>
          <td>Standard 3D vector</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>geometry_msgs/msg/Pose</td>
          <td>position: Point (x, y, z)<br>orientation: Quaternion (x, y, z, w)</td>
          <td>Pose of a reference frame (TF)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>geometry_msgs/msg/Point</td>
          <td>x: float64<br>y: float64<br>z: float64</td>
          <td>3D position without orientation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>geometry_msgs/msg/Quaternion</td>
          <td>x: float64<br>y: float64<br>z: float64<br>w: float64</td>
          <td>Orientation representation<br>via quaternion</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>geometry_msgs/msg/Twist</td>
          <td>linear: Vector3 (x, y, z)<br>angular: Vector3 (x, y, z)</td>
          <td>Linear and angular velocity<br>of a reference frame (TF)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>geometry_msgs/msg/Accel</td>
          <td>linear: Vector3<br>angular: Vector3</td>
          <td>Linear and angular acceleration<br>of a reference frame (TF)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>geometry_msgs/msg/Wrench</td>
          <td>force: Vector3<br>torque: Vector3</td>
          <td>Force and moment<br>at a reference frame (TF)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>sensor_msgs/msg/JointState</td>
          <td>header: Header<br>name: string[]<br>position: float64[]<br>velocity: float64[]<br>effort: float64[]</td>
          <td>Joint feedback: positions,<br>velocities, and joint torques</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>example_interfaces/srv/Trigger</td>
          <td>Request: (empty)<br>Response: success: bool, message: string</td>
          <td>Trigger an action<br>without input (e.g., reset)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>example_interfaces/srv/SetBool</td>
          <td>Request: data: bool<br>Response: success: bool, message: string</td>
          <td>Enable/disable<br>a feature or mode</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.3.2 Importing Interfaces &amp; Actions Into Nodes</h3>
  <p>You must import interfaces within node scripts. <strong>Don't forget to add the packages which your interfaces come from to the dependencies of your own package under its CMakeLists.txt and package.xml files.</strong></p>

  <h4 class="subsection-heading">7.3.2.1 Python</h4>
  <p>For subscribers or publishers:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={pyImportMsgCode} lang="python" customHtml={pyImportMsgCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p>For servers or clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={pyImportSrvCode} lang="python" customHtml={pyImportSrvCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p>For action servers &amp; action clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={pyImportActionCode} lang="python" customHtml={pyImportActionCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> <code class="ph-type">[msg_type]</code>, <code class="ph-type">[srv_type]</code> or <code class="ph-type">[action_type]</code> will be simply the name of the .msg, .srv or .action file - <strong>first letters in every word are capitalized and there are no underscores.</strong></p>
  
  <p>Example:</p>
  <CodeBlock code="SensorStatus" lang="text" />

  <h4 class="subsection-heading">7.3.2.2 C++</h4>
  <p>For subscribers or publishers:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cppImportMsgCode} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppImportMsgCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p>For servers or clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cppImportSrvCode} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppImportSrvCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p>For action servers &amp; action clients:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cppImportActionCode} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppImportActionCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> in #include, <strong><code class="ph-type">[msg_type]</code>, <code class="ph-type">[srv_type]</code> or <code class="ph-type">[action_type]</code> must be minuscule and the words separated by underscores</strong>. More specifically, the words in <code class="ph-type">[msg_type]</code>, <code class="ph-type">[srv_type]</code> or <code class="ph-type">[action_type]</code> were specified as starting with capital letters when creating the .msg, .srv or .action file names.</p>

  <p>Example:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={'#include "custom_interfaces/msg/sensor_status.hpp"'} lang="cpp" />

  <p><strong>NOTE:</strong>  in #include, words separated by numbers within <code class="ph-type">[msg_type]</code>, <code class="ph-type">[srv_type]</code> or <code class="ph-type">[action_type]</code> will not have underscores between them.</p>

  <p>Example:</p>
  <CodeBlock code={`// Message type is custom_interfaces/msg/Pose3dFeedback in ROS\n#include "custom_interfaces/msg/pose3d_feedback.hpp"`} lang="cpp" />

  <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> while calling the interfaces in the C++ program, <strong><code class="ph-type">[srv_type]</code> uses capital letters at the beginning of words and no underscores (like in the .msg or .srv file names)</strong>.</p>

  <p>Example:</p>
  <CodeBlock code="custom_interfaces::msg::SensorStatus" lang="cpp" />


  <h2 class="section-heading" id="storing-interfaces">7.4 Storing Custom Interfaces &amp; Action Types</h2>
  <p>Create a C++ package for the custom message interface, as per <strong><a href="/packages">Section 3</a></strong>. No dependencies are needed. You may remove the /src directory within the package, since it is not essential.</p>

  <CodeBlock code="rm -r include/ src/" lang="bash" />

  <p>Include the following in the package.xml file, right before the &lt;test_depend&gt; lines.</p>
  <CodeBlock code={`<buildtool_depend>rosidl_default_generators</buildtool_depend>\n<exec_depend>rosidl_default_runtime</exec_depend>\n<member_of_group>rosidl_interface_packages</member_of_group>`} lang="xml" />

  <p>Replace the CMakeList.txt file with the following.</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cmakeInitCode} lang="cmake" customHtml={cmakeInitCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.4.1 Directory to Store Message Interfaces</h3>
  <p>Create a new directory within your custom interfaces package (/src/<code class="ph-generic">[package_name]</code>).</p>
  <CodeBlock code="mkdir msg" lang="bash" />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.4.2 Directory to Store Server Interfaces</h3>
  <p>Create a new directory within your custom interfaces package (/src/<code class="ph-generic">[package_name]</code>).</p>
  <CodeBlock code="mkdir srv" lang="bash" />

  <h3 class="subsection-heading">7.4.3 Directory to Store Action Types</h3>
  <p>Create a new directory within your custom interfaces package (/src/<code class="ph-generic">[package_name]</code>).</p>
  <CodeBlock code="mkdir action" lang="bash" />


  <h2 class="section-heading" id="custom-messages">7.5 Custom Message Interfaces</h2>
  <p>Create a new file within your message interfaces directory (/src/<code class="ph-generic">[package_name]</code>/msg). Its title will be the name of the message type (interface) you wish to create.</p>

  <CodeBlock code={touchMsgCode} lang="bash" customHtml={touchMsgCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p><strong>NOTE: Make sure that <code class="ph-type">[msg_type]</code> has no underscores, and that every first letter in each word is capitalized.</strong></p>
  <p>ex: SensorStatus.msg</p>

  <p>In this file, use the following format to organize message variables.</p>
  <CodeBlock code={msgStructureCode} lang="text" customHtml={msgStructureCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p>You will most often use the primitive data types from <strong><a href="#data-types">Section 7.1</a></strong>.</p>
  <p><strong>NOTE: the message variables must be all minuscule and separated by underscores.</strong></p>

  <p>Include any message interfaces created into the CMakeLists.txt file for the package you created for custom interfaces.</p>
  <CodeBlock code={cmakeAddMsgCode} lang="cmake" customHtml={cmakeAddMsgCustom} showLegend={true} />

